id: pm-ols6
title: Centralize audit ownership-conflict guidance
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: append-only/audit override commands repeat the same ownership-conflict catch predicate and guidance wrapping. Representative blocks are in src/cli/commands/learnings.ts:122, src/cli/commands/notes.ts:118, src/cli/commands/comments.ts:196, and src/cli/commands/claim.ts:131. Each checks PmCliError conflict text, then throws a new PmCliError with code ownership_conflict plus command-specific required/examples/nextSteps. This is not included in pm-why9's CLI parser/update-table scope. Fix by extracting a helper that recognizes mutateItem assignee conflicts and formats command-specific audit guidance without changing current messages."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: code-quality,dedup,ownership
created_at: "2026-05-22T18:54:47.501Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T01:58:51.740Z"
author: codex-duplicate-audit
acceptance_criteria: "A shared helper owns the assignee-conflict recognition and PmCliError wrapping; comments, notes, learnings, and release/claim audit override paths keep their current user-facing guidance; tests cover at least one command-specific message and one pass-through non-conflict error; pnpm build and targeted command tests pass."
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Closed by extracting the shared ownership conflict wrapper.
expected_result: Append-only audit commands and release share the ownership-conflict predicate and wrapping while keeping command-specific guidance text.
actual_result: "wrapOwnershipConflict now centralizes the predicate/wrapping; comments, notes, learnings, and release use it; focused tests, manual dogfood, validate, and full release gate passed."
comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-22T18:54:47.501Z",codex-duplicate-audit,"Duplicate-check evidence: searched tracker for ownership/allow-audit conflict dedup. Existing pm-why9 does not mention this path; no specific open item found. Code scan found the same catch predicate across comments, notes, learnings, and claim/release logic."
  "2026-05-24T01:29:17.010Z",codex-ownership-specialist,"Investigation note: ownership/author-helper specialist explorer pass starting. Scope: inspect mutation author resolution and ownership conflict guidance across append/comments/notes/learnings/files/docs/delete/history-redact/claim plus shared CLI helpers; no file edits."
  "2026-05-24T01:30:36.491Z",codex-ownership-specialist,"Investigation finding: propose shared helper wrapOwnershipConflict(error, guidance) in CLI/shared layer. Recognition must stay exactly: PmCliError + EXIT_CODE.CONFLICT + message contains 'is assigned to' and 'Use --force to override'. It should rethrow non-matches unchanged and wrap matches with code=ownership_conflict plus command-owned required/examples/nextSteps. Stable current command semantics: comments require --allow-audit-comment; notes require --allow-audit-note with legacy --allow-audit-comment; learnings require --allow-audit-learning with legacy --allow-audit-comment; release requires --allow-audit-release. Keep existing required/example/nextSteps text byte-for-byte unless a separate UX item changes it."
  "2026-05-24T01:36:09.589Z",codex-active-work,"Evidence: ownership conflict recognition and PmCliError guidance wrapping now lives in wrapOwnershipConflict inside src/cli/commands/annotation-command.ts. comments/notes/learnings and release keep command-specific required/examples/nextSteps text while sharing the exact conflict predicate. Focused tests passed: comments-command, notes-learnings-command, and help-runtime specs (62 tests)."
  "2026-05-24T01:58:26.554Z",codex-active-work,"Final verification evidence: shared ownership conflict wrapper is covered by focused ownership tests plus final release gate. node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs passed with 105 files / 1583 tests / 100 percent coverage, secret scan, compatibility, package dogfood, and required Sentry/telemetry gate (critical=0 high=2, telemetry error rate=2.94, missing error-code rows=0)."
